description.p:
In the present invention, as one means for making the electric resistance in the fixing area 25 relatively lower compared with that in the non-fixing area 26, a means for making the fiber occupation ratio in the fixing area 25 relatively higher compared with that in the non-fixing area 26 upon the holding of the substrate laminate by the shaping mold can be employed. When the fiber occupation ratio in the fixing area 25 is made higher, the fibers existing in the vicinity of the area can be closely adhered and therefore the number of passages through which an electric current can flow can be increased in the area. As a result, the electric resistance in the fixing area 25 can be reduced. The term "a fiber occupation ratio (Vf)" as used herein refers to a value determined in accordance with the following formula (unit: %). Vf%=W×n/ρ×T×10 wherein
W: the mass of the reinforcing fiber substrates per 1 m2 (g/m2);
n: the number of the reinforcing fiber substrates laminated;
p: the density of the reinforcing fibers (g/cm3); and
T: the distance between the molds (mm).
